rComments: Prof Goudreau est bonne. Pas bcp de lectures, bcp de pratiques avant lexamen. Lexamen comme tel est très long et un peu difficile mais tout le monde passe son cours.
Do NOT write an exam in her class. Write a paper/several papers/do a presentation with her, she is a fair grader and appreciates hard work. Great lecturer and interesting material.

If she offers doing optional take-home papers, do them. Really harsh grader on exams - exams are really long and the questions are very poorly written. Great at teaching content, but you'll probably still get a horrible grade if the final exam is worth 100% of your grade. Lots of content, lots of readings, very abstract concepts.

Undoubtedly one of the best teachers in the Law Faculty. She is passionate, makes interesting material even more interesting, can answer every single question with ease and clarity - a real role model for any future teacher or aspiring lawyer. The exam is not easy, but which law exam is? With sufficient time and effort you will do just fine. A+PROF
Awesome teacher! She is definitely in the top 3 best teachers of the Civil Law UofO faculty! She is dynamic, has clear powerpoints, exercises and is a generous grader.  Overall, very fair teacher.
Professeure extraordinaire qui connait sa matière. Ses examens sont difficiles mais sa correction est juste.
